{"parse":{"title":"drink","pageid":3162,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Drink}}\n==English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|dhrink||pronunciation spelling|imitating an Irish accent}}\n* {{alt|en|drank||slang|[[w:Thank-think merger|thank-think merger]]}}\n* {{alt|en|drinck|drinke||obsolete}}\n* {{alt|en|thrink||pronunciation spelling}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈdɹɪŋk/|[ˈd͡ɹ̝ʷɪŋk]|~|[ˈd̠͡ɹ̠˔ʷɪŋk]}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Naomi Persephone Amethyst (NaomiAmethyst)-drink.wav|a=US}}\n* {{a|en|pre-/ŋ/-tensing}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈdɹiŋk/|[d͡ɹ̝ʷiŋk]|~|[ˈd̠͡ɹ̠˔ʷiŋk]|;|[d͡ɹ̝ʷɪ̝ŋk]|~|[ˈd̠͡ɹ̠˔ʷɪ̝ŋk]|a=Upper Midwestern US,Western US,CA}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-us-drink.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{a|en|Appalachian|AAVE|[[w:Thank-think merger|thank-think merger]]}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈdɹæŋk/|[ˈd͡ɹ̝ʷæŋk]|~|[ˈd̠͡ɹ̠˔ʷæŋk]|a=non-æ-tensing}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈdɹeɪ̯ŋk/|[d͡ɹ̝ʷeɪ̯ŋk]|~|[ˈd̠͡ɹ̠˔ʷeɪ̯ŋk]|;|/ˈdɹɛ̃ŋk/|[d͡ɹ̝ʷɛ̃ŋk]|~|[ˈd̠͡ɹ̠˔ʷɛ̃ŋk]|a=æ-tensing}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɪŋk|s=1}}\n* {{hyph|en|drink}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|en|id=verb|:inh|enm:drinken}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|drinken}}, from {{inh|en|ang|drincan|t=to drink, swallow up, engulf}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*drinkan}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*drinkaną|t=to drink}}, of uncertain origin; possibly from {{der|en|ine-pro|*dʰrenǵ-|t=to draw into one's mouth, sip, gulp}}, nasalised variant of {{m|ine-pro|*dʰreǵ-|t=to draw, glide}}.\n\n{{col-top|2|cog}}\nCognate with {{cog|yol|drink|t=to drink}}, {{cog|frr|drank}}, {{m|frr|drainke}}, {{m|frr|drink}}, {{m|frr|drinke|t=to drink}}, {{cog|fy|drinke|t=to drink}}, {{cog|gsw|trénge}}, {{m|gsw|trenhu}}, {{m|gsw|trinche}}, {{m|gsw|tringhien}}, {{m|gsw|trinke|t=to drink}}, {{cog|bar|dringa}}, {{m|bar|trinckn}}, {{m|bar|trinkhn}}, {{m|bar|trinkn|t=to drink}}, {{cog|cim|trinkan}}, {{m|cim|trinkhan|t=to drink}}, {{cog|nl,nds|drinken|t=to drink}}, {{cog|de,mhn|trinken|t=to drink}}, {{cog|lb|drénken|t=to drink}}, {{cog|yi|טרינקען|t=to drink}}, {{cog|da,nb|drikke|t=to drink}}, {{cog|ovd|drikka|t=to drink}}, {{cog|fo,is|drekka|t=to drink}}, {{cog|jut|drenk|t=to drink}}, {{cog|nn|drikka}}, {{m|nn|drikke|t=to drink}}, {{cog|sv|dricka|t=to drink}}, {{cog|got|𐌳𐍂𐌹𐌲𐌺𐌰𐌽|t=to drink}}, {{cog|xvn|drincan|t=to drink}}, {{cog|fr|trinquer|t=to booze, drink alcohol}}, {{cog|it|trincare|t=to knock back (a drink)}}, {{cog|es|trincar|t=to get drunk}}.\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Verb====\n[[Image:Woman drinking water.jpg|thumb|Woman '''drinking''' a glass of water]]\n{{en-verb|~s|~ing|drank,drunk<l:Southern US>,~ed<l:nonstandard>|drunk,drunken<l:chiefly,archaic>,drank<l:dialectal>,~ed<l:all,nonstandard,archaic,or,obsolete>,~en,dranken}}\n\n# {{lb|en|ambitransitive}} To [[consume]] (a liquid) through the mouth.\n#: {{syn|en|gulp|imbibe|quaff|sip|see [[Thesaurus:drink]]}}\n#: {{ux|en|He '''drank''' the water I gave him.}}\n#: {{ux|en|You can lead a horse to water but you can't make him '''drink'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Spenser Shepheardes Calender|chapter=November|folio=47|passage={{...}} There liues ſhee with the bleſſed Gods in bliſſe: / There '''drinks''' the Nectar with Ambroſia mixt {{...}}|year=1586}}\n#* {{RQ:Thackeray Virginians|volume=I|page=283|passage=It was he who proposed the bowl of punch, which was brewed and '''drunk''' in Mrs. Betty’s room, and which Gumbo concocted with exquisite skill.}}\n#* {{RQ:Maxwell Mirror and the Lamp|chapter=2|passage=''That'' the young Mr. Churchills liked—but they did not like him coming round of an evening and '''drinking''' weak whisky-and-water while he held forth on railway debentures and corporation loans. Mr. Barrett, however, by fawning and flattery, seemed to be able to make not only Mrs. Churchill but everyone else do what he desired.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|metonymic}} To [[consume]] the liquid contained within (a bottle, glass, etc.).\n#: {{ux|en|Jack '''drank''' the whole bottle by himself.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[consume]] [[alcoholic]] [[beverage]]s.\n#: {{syn|en|drink [[alcohol]]|booze#Verb}}\n#: {{near-syn|en|hit the bottle|hit the sauce}}\n#: {{ux|en|You've been '''drinking''', haven't you?}}\n#: {{ux|en|No thanks, I don't '''drink'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Everyone who is '''drinking''' is drinking, but not everyone who is drinking is '''drinking'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Macbeth|III|iv|passage=I '''drink''' to the general joy of the whole table, / And to our dear friend Banquo.}}\n#* {{RQ:Thackeray Henry Esmond|passage=Bolingbroke always spoke freely when he had '''drunk''' freely.}}\n#* {{RQ:Salinger Catcher|page=168|passage=The waiter came up, and I ordered a Coke for her—she didn't '''drink'''—and a Scotch and soda for myself, but the sonuvabitch wouldn't bring me one, so I had a Coke, too.}}\n#* {{quote-av|en|year=2007|writer=w:Matthew Weiner|title=w:Mad Men|episode=Smoke Gets in Your Eyes|season=1|number=1|role=w:Roger Sterling|actor=|passage=You don't know how to '''drink'''. Your whole generation, you '''drink''' for the wrong reasons. My generation, we '''drink''' because it's good, because it feels better than unbuttoning your collar, because we deserve it. We '''drink''' because it's what men do.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To take in (a liquid), in any manner; to suck up; to absorb; to imbibe.\n#* {{RQ:Dryden Georgics|4|passage=Let the purple violets '''drink''' the stream.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To take in; to receive within one, through the senses; to inhale; to hear; to see.\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Romeo and Juliet|II|ii|passage=My ears have not yet '''drunk''' a hundred words / Of that tongue's utterance.}}\n#* {{RQ:Pope Works|title=Eloisa to Abelard|Let me {{...}} '''drink''' delicious poison from thy eye.}}\n#* {{RQ:Tennyson In Memoriam|passage=to '''drink''' the cooler air}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|archaic}} To [[toast#Verb|toast]] (someone or something) with a drink, [[honour#Verb|honour]]; to [[wish well]] (see [[drink to]]), especially:\n#* {{RQ:Tennyson Works|II|The Vision of Sin|131|part=iv|Drink to lofty hopes that cool —<br>Visions of a perfect State : '''Drink''' we, last, the public fool,<br>Frantic love and frantic hate.}}\n## To express one's desire for the accomplishment of a toast, sentiment or event, to [[wish#Verb|wish]], [[hope]] (for), [[forward#Verb|forward]] (especially as 'to drink the health (of someone)').\n##* {{quote-book|en|author={{w|Thomas Hearne (antiquarian)|Thomas Hearne}}|title=Remarks and Collections of Thomas Hearne|1710|text=At the same time were great Acclamations & they '''drunk''' Damnation to D{{sup|r}}. Sacheverell, M{{sup|r}} Tilly, and all the D{{sup|rs}} friends.}}\n##* {{RQ:Spectator|author=Steele|date=19 December 1712|issue=433|text=I ought not to have neglected a request of one of my correspondents so long as I have; but I dare say I have given him time to add practice to profession. He sent me some time ago a bottle or two of excellent wine to '''drink the health''' of a gentleman had by the penny post advertised him of an egregious error in his conduct. {{...}}}}\n## {{lb|en|obsolete|with [[carouse#Noun|carouse]]}} {{+obj|en|to<someone or something>}}\n##* {{RQ:Shakespeare Antony and Cleopatra|IV|viii|360-361|2-1|Had our great Pall ace the capacity<br>To Campe this hoſt, we all would ſup together,<br>And '''drinke''' Carowſes to the next dayes Fate<br>Which promiſes Royall perill, Trumpetters<br>With brazen dinne blaſt you the Cittics eare,<br>Make mingle with our ratling Tabourines,<br>That heauen and earth may ſtrike their ſounds together,<br>Applauding our approach.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|obsolete}} To [[smoke]], as [[tobacco]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1630|author={{w|John Taylor (poet)|Taylor, John (\"The Water Poet\", 1578{{ndash}}1653)}}|title=A Proclomation or approbation from the King of execration, to euery nation, for Tobaccoes propogration|passage=And some men now live ninety yeeres and past,<br />Who never '''dranke''' tobacco first nor last.}}\n# {{used in phrasal verbs|drink down|drink in|drink off|drink out|drink to|drink up|lang=en}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|title=Terms derived from {{m|en|drink|pos=verb}}|bedrink|drinkable|drink and drive|drinker|drinking<pos:noun, adjective>|drinkle|drink like a fish|drink someone under the table|drink up|undrink|drink from a firehose|drink down|drink under|drink in|drink oneself to death|drink one's own Kool-Aid|drink off|drink out|drink something like lemonade|drink the Kool-Aid|drink to|drink with the flies|I'll drink to that|piss more than one drinks|drinking straw|drinking water|drinking-cup|drive someone to drink|preach water and drink wine|ready-to-drink|drink under the table|drink from the fire hydrant|nondrinking|drincc|drinkability|drinkathon|drinkware|outdrink|overdrink|redrink|undrinkability|drink from the furry cup|day-drink|drink someone's bathwater}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|en|drunken}}, {{l|en|drunk}}, {{l|en|dranken}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|bzj|jrink}}\n* {{desc|cpi|drinkee|alts=1}}\n* {{desc|srn|dringi}}\n** {{desc|djk|diingi}}\n** {{desc|srm|diíngi}}\n* {{desc|tpi|dringim|der=1}}\n* {{desc|eo|drinki|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|io|drinkar|bor=1}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|consume liquid through the mouth}}\n{{multitrans|data=\n* Abkhaz: {{t|ab|ажәра}}\n* Acehnese: {{t-needed|ace}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|drink}}\n* Akan: {{t|ak|nom}}\n* Akkadian: {{t|akk|𒅘|tr=[[Image:B064ellst.png|40px]], ''šatû'', NAG}}\n* Aklanon: {{t|akl|inom}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|pi}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|ичер}}\n* American Sign Language: {{t|ase|C@NearMouth-TipForward C@NearMouth-TipUp}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am|መጠጣት}}\n* Ao: {{t|njo|ajem}} {{q|Chungli}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|شَرِبَ}}\n*: Chadian Arabic: {{t|shu|شرب|tr=širib}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|شرب|tr=širib}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|شِرِب|tr=širib}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|شْرب|tr=šrab}}\n* Aragonese: {{t+|an|beber}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Syriac: {{t|syc|ܫܬܐ|tr=šθa}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|ըմպել}}, {{t+|hy|խմել}}\n* Aromanian: {{t+|rup|beau}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|খা}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|beber}}, {{t+|ast|tomar}}\n* Aukan: {{t|djk|diingi}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|içmək}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|эсеү}}\n* Basque: {{t+|eu|edan}}\n* Bedjond: {{t|bjv|à̰ȳ}}\n* Belarusian: {{t+|be|піць|impf}}, {{t|be|вы́піць|pf}}\n* Belizean Creole: {{t|bzj|jrink}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|খাওয়া}}, {{t+|bn|পিয়া}}\n* Besisi: {{t|mhe|cado}}\n* Bhojpuri: {{t|bho|पिअल}}\n* Bidayuh:\n*: Biatah Bidayuh: {{t|bth|nok}}\n*: Bukar-Sadung Bidayuh: {{t|sdo|sihip}}\n* Brahui: {{t|brh|kunak}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|evañ}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|пи́я|impf}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|သောက်}}\n* Buryat: {{t|bua|ууха}}\n* Carpathian Rusyn: {{t|rue|пи́ти|impf}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|beure}}\n* Cebuano: {{t|ceb|inom}}\n* Chakma: {{t-needed|ccp}}\n* Cham:\n*: Eastern Cham: {{t|cjm|ꨟꨐꨭꩌ|tr=mưnhum}}\n* Chechen: {{t|ce|мала}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|mwa|alt=kumwá}}, {{t|ny|nyota|alt=kunyóta}}\n* Chickasaw: {{t|cic|ishko}}\n* Chin:\n*: Tedim Chin: {{t|ctd|dawn}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|飲|tr=jam2}}, {{t|yue|呷}}\n*: Dungan: {{t|dng|хә}}\n*: Eastern Min: {{t|cdo|啜|tr=chiók}}\n*: Gan: {{t|gan|吃}}\n*: Hakka: {{t|hak|食|tr=sṳ̍t}}\n*: Hokkien: {{t+|nan-hbl|啉|tr=lim}}\n*: Jin: {{t|cjy|喝}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|喝|tr=hē}}, {{q|{{lg|literary}}}} {{t+|cmn|飲|tr=yǐn}}\n*: Wu: {{t|wuu|吃}}\n*: Xiang: {{t|hsn|吃|tr=qia6}}\n* Chinook Jargon: {{t|chn|loqa}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|eva}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|pít|impf}}\n* Dalmatian: {{t|dlm|bar}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|drikke}}\n* Drung: {{t|duu|ngaq}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|drinken}}\n* Egyptian: {{t-egy|zwr|h=z:wr:r-A2}}\n* Elfdalian: {{t|ovd|drikka}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|trinki}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|jooma}}\n* Evenki: {{t|evn|уммӣ|pf}}, {{t|evn|умдямӣ|impf}}\n* Fang (Bantu): {{t|fan|áñú}}\n* Faroese: {{t+|fo|drekka}}\n* Fijian: {{t+|fj|gunuva}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|juoda}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|boire}}\n* Frisian:\n*: North Frisian:\n*:: Föhr: {{t|frr|drank}}\n*:: Halligen: {{t|frr|drinke}}\n*:: Mooring: {{t|frr|drainke}}\n*: Old Frisian: {{t|ofs|drinka}}\n*: West Frisian: {{t|fy|drinke}}\n* Friulian: {{t|fur|bevi}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|beber}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|სმა}}, {{t|ka|დალევა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|trinken}}, {{t+|de|saufen}} {{qualifier|for animals}}\n*: Alemannic German: {{t|gsw|trinke}}\n*: Middle High German: {{t|gmh|trinken}}\n*: Old High German: {{t|goh|trinkan}}\n*: Swabian: {{t|swg|schlotza}}\n* Gothic: {{t|got|𐌳𐍂𐌹𐌲𐌺𐌰𐌽}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|πίνω}} {{qualifier|used for animals also}}, {{t+|el|απορροφώ}} {{qualifier|used for plants}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|πίνω}}\n*: Doric Greek: {{t|grc|πώνω}}\n* Greenlandic: {{t|kl|imerpoq}}\n* Gujarati: {{t|gu|પીવું}}\n* Haitian Creole: {{t|ht|bwè}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|inu}}, {{t|haw|inumia}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|שָׁתָה|tr=shatá}}, {{t+|he|גָּמַע|tr=gamá'}}\n* Higaonon: {{t|mba|inom}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|पीना}}, {{t+|hi|सोखना}}\n* Hmong:\n*: White Hmong: {{t|mww|haus}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|iszik}}\n* Hunsrik: {{t|hrx|drinke}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|drekka}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|drinkar}}\n* Igbo: {{t|ig|nuo}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|minum}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|joovva}}\n* Ingush: {{t|inh|мала}}\n* Interlingua: {{t+|ia|biber}}\n* Inuktitut: {{t|iu|ᐃᒥᖅᑐᖅ}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|ól}}, {{t|ga|ibh}} {{qualifier|literary}}\n*: Old Irish: {{t|sga|ibid}}\n* Isnag: {{t|isd|inum}}\n* Isoko: {{t|iso|da}}\n* Istro-Romanian: {{t|ruo|be}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|bere}}\n* Iu Mien: {{t|ium|hopv}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|飲む|tr=のむ, nomu}}, {{t+|ja|召し上がる|tr=めしあがる, meshiagaru}} {{qualifier|honorific}}, {{t+|ja|頂く|tr=いただく, itadaku}} {{qualifier|humble}}\n* Jarai: {{t|jra|mơñum}}\n* Javanese: {{t+|jv|ngombé}} {{qualifier|casual}}, {{t+|jv|ngunjuk}} {{qualifier|polite}}, {{t+|jv|mimik}} {{qualifier|children}}\n* Jeju: {{t|jje|먹다}}, {{t|jje|마시다}}\n* Jingpho: {{t|kac|lu}}\n* Jutish: {{t|jut|drek}}\n* Kalmyk: {{t|xal|уух}}\n* Karakhanid: {{t|xqa|اِجْماكْ|tr=ičmēk}}\n* Kashmiri: {{t|ks|چۆن}}\n* Kashubian: {{t|csb|pic}}\n* Kazakh: {{t+|kk|ішу}}\n* Khakas: {{t|kjh|ізерге}}, {{t|kjh|ічерге}} {{qualifier|dialectal}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|ផឹក}}\n* Kituba: {{t|ktu|nwa}}, {{t|ktu|k