}, {{t+|sv|supa}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|inom}}, {{t|tl|tagay}}, {{t+|tl|toma}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|తాగు}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|ดื่ม}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|içmek}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|[[uống]] [[rượu]]}}, {{t|vi|[[uống]] [[say]]}}, {{t+|vi|nhậu}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|llymeitian}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|mutí}}\n* Zealandic: {{t|zea|drienke}}, {{t|zea|zupe}}\n* Zulu: {{t|zu|qhafa|alt=-qhafa}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Breton: {{t+check|br|evañ}}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{qualifier|vt}} {{t-check|gug|'u}}, {{qualifier|vi}} {{t-check|gug|y'u}}\n* Interlingua: {{t+check|ia|biber}}\n* Kannada: {{t+check|kn|ಕುಡಿ}}, {{t+check|kn|ಹೀರು}}\n* Khmer: {{t+check|km|ផឹក}}, {{t-check|km|ទទួលទាន}}\n* Low German: {{t+check|nds|drinken}}, {{t+check|nds|supen}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+check|sa|पानम्}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t-check|si|පේනා}}, {{t-check|si|පේනවා}}\n* Slovak: {{t+check|sk|piť}}\n* Tamil: {{t+check|ta|குடி}}\n* Volapük: {{t-check|vo|dlinön}}, {{t+check|vo|drinön}}\n* Welsh: {{t+check|cy|yfed}}\n* Woiwurrung: {{t-check|wyi|ngupa}}\n* Xhosa: {{t-check|xh|ukusela}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymon|en|id=noun|:inh|enm:drink<ety:inh<ang:drynċ>>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|drink}}, {{m|enm|drinke}} (also as {{m|enm|drinche}}, {{m|enm|drunch}}), from {{inh|en|ang|drynċ}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*drunkiz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*drankiz}}.\n{{col-top|2|cog}}\nCognate with {{cog|stq|Dronk|t=drink}}, {{cog|cim|gatrànkh|t=drink}}, {{cog|nl|drank}}, {{m|nl|dronk|t=drink}}, {{cog|de|Getränk}}, {{m|de|trank}}, {{m|de|Trunk|t=drink}}, {{cog|nds-de|Drank}}, {{m|nds|Drunk|t=drink}}, {{cog|wym|gytrenḱ|t=drink}}, {{cog|da|drik|t=drink, beverage}}, {{cog|is|drykkur|t=drink, beverage}}, {{cog|nb|drikk|t=drink}}, {{cog|nn|drikk}}, {{m|nn|drykk|t=drink, alcohol}}, {{cog|sv|dryck|t=drink}}, {{cog|got|𐌳𐍂𐌰𐌲𐌲𐌺}}, {{m|got|𐌳𐍂𐌰𐌲𐌺|t=drink}}.\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q40050}}A [[beverage]].\n#: {{ux|en|I’d like another '''drink''' please.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} Drinks in general; something to drink.\n#* {{RQ:King James Version|book=Matthew|chapter=25|verse=35|passage=For I was an hungred, and ye gave me meat: I was thirsty, and ye gave me '''drink'''}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|last=Sullivan|first=Ceri|date=6 September 2024|title=Shakespeare’s Will, Lambswool, and Puck’s Joke|journal=w:Notes and Queries|volume=71|issue=4|page=406|publisher=w:Oxford University Press|doi=10.1093/notesj/gjae116|passage=These sources do not, however, state why the drink is called lambswool. The name comes from the way the apples are roasted until they split open, and their pulp froths over the skin; this is used to float on top of the bowl of '''drink'''.}}\n# A type of [[beverage]] (usually mixed).\n#: {{ux|en|My favourite '''drink''' is the White Russian.}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q154}} A ([[serve]]d) alcoholic [[beverage]].\n#: {{hyper|en|beverage<id:Q40050>}}\n#: {{ux|en|Can I buy you a '''drink'''?}}\n# The action of [[drinking]], especially with the verbs ''[[take]]'' or ''[[have]]''.\n#: {{ux|en|He was about to take a '''drink''' from his root beer.}}\n# [[alcohol|Alcoholic]] [[beverage]]s in general.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1935|author=[https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/288354.George_Goodchild George Goodchild]\n|title=Death on the Centre Court|chapter=1\n|passage=She mixed furniture with the same fatal profligacy as she mixed '''drinks''', and this outrageous contact between things which were intended by Nature to be kept poles apart gave her an inexpressible thrill.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=10 Feb 79|volume=6|number=28|journal=Gay Community News|page=11|title=An American Dream|author=Michael Bronski|text=By the late twenties father has died of '''drink''' and his wife is left to raise their two sons.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=1995|artist=w:Bruce McCulloch|album=Shame-Based Man|track=12|title=Daddy's on the '''Drink'''|url=https://genius.com/Bruce-mcculloch-daddys-on-the-drink-lyrics|passage=The face of work is a drunk man in the same chair, chewing on the same bone for five thousand nights. The face of work is a, coffee cup in hand, frustrated: \"You don't get it. They all don't get it. You don't understand, man.\" Daddy's on the '''drink''' again.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=w:Blake Bailey|title='Tennessee Williams,' by John Lahr &#91;print version: Theatrical victory of art over life, ''International New York Times'', 18 November 2014, p.&nbsp;13&#93;|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/16/books/review/tennessee-williams-by-john-lahr.html|work=w:The New York Times|date=14 November 2014|passage={{...}} she was indeed Amanda in the flesh: a doughty chatterbox from Ohio who adopted the manner of a Southern belle and eschewed both '''drink''' and sex to the greatest extent possible.}}\n# A [[standard drink]].\n#: {{ux|en|A '''drink''' of wine is about 5 ounces}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1963|title=Vital and Health Statistics: Programs and collection procedures|page=125|text=And when (SUBJECT) was 55, would you say (he/she) drank more than, less than, or about 2 to 3 '''drinks''' a day?}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial|with ''the''}} Any body of water.\n#: {{ux|en|If he doesn't pay off the mafia, he’ll wear cement shoes to the bottom of the '''drink'''!}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|year=1996\n|author=John French+\n|title=A Drop in the Ocean: Dramatic Accounts of Aircrew Saved From the Sea\n|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=lgSSAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT99\n|isbn=9781473813809\n|page=99\n|publisher=Pen and Sword\n|1=en\n|passage=When in mid-Channel the speed slowed and I was informed by A.C. Russell that another dinghy had been spotted. This turned out to contain a Canadian fighter pilot who had been in the '''drink''' for three days and was in rather a bad way. He said he had seen all the aircraft flying over in the two days before D-Day and since, but no one had sighted him.}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|year=2011\n|author=Levi Johnston\n|title=Deer in the Headlights: My Life in Sarah Palin's Crosshairs\n|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=g9eNWzfPx8IC&pg=PT34\n|isbn=9781451651676\n|page=34\n|publisher=Simon and Schuster\n|1=en\n|passage=In seconds, we went from sitting in a boat to threading ice-cold water. I wasn't wearing a life jacket and am not the best paddler, but there I was, in the '''drink''', splashing around.}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|year=2012\n|author=Jack R. Myers\n|title=Shot at and Missed: Recollections of a World War II Bombardier\n|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=93PZi5CSZ0AC&pg=PT31\n|isbn=9780806184890\n|page=31\n|publisher=University of Oklahoma Press\n|1=en\n|passage=If the planes couldn't make it, they would go in the '''drink''', eject their rubber lifeboats, inflate them, climb in, and pray for the Navy to pick them up before the Germans did.}}\n# {{lb|en|Australia|figurative}} A [[downpour]]; a [[cloudburst]]; a [[rainstorm]]; a [[deluge]]; a lot of [[rain]].\n#* {{quote-av|en|speaker=Nate Byrne|title=[[:w:News Breakfast|News Breakfast]]|season=2023|number=74|publisher=[[:w:ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]]|date=13 April 2023|at=07:56 am (UTC+10/AEST)|location=Melbourne, Australia|text=Now this is going to bring some huge totals of rainfall with it—200 to 400 millimetres with it—and along with that, these winds—gusts to 275 kilometres an hour near the cyclone &#91;[[:w:Cyclone Ilsa|Cyclone Ilsa]]&#93; core—and that's a real concern. That's very destructive winds and it's going to carry this inertia and the rain with it well inland. And we're likely going to be talking about a cyclone all the way through Friday as it slowly weakens, eventually washing that moisture out into a front going through the south. It means the southeast is getting a '''drink''' but [[Western Australia|W.A.]]'s northwest really copping it, individual totals significantly higher than what you're seeing here [on the weather map].}}\n# {{lb|en|informal}} {{1|amount}}.\n#* {{quote-video game|en|year=2004|title=w:Paper Mario: The Thousand-Year Door|developer=Intelligent Systems|publisher=Nintendo|system=GameCube|level=|translator=Nintendo of America|text=He [a sea-serpent] was giant, massive. A huge '''drink''' of man-eater. But even now, you know, I could take him.}}\n\n=====Usage notes=====\n* A plainer term than more elevated {{m|en|beverage}}. '''Beverage''' is of French origin, while ''drink'' is of Old English origin, and this stylistic difference by origin is common; see {{w|list of English words with dual French and Anglo-Saxon variations}}.\n* In the sense of ''any body of water'' the term is often associated with (a threat of) [[drowning]].\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|served beverage}} ''See'' [[Thesaurus:beverage]]\n* {{sense|alcoholic beverage, served or in general}} ''See'' [[Thesaurus:alcoholic beverage]]\n* {{sense|action of drinking}} {{l|en|gulp}}, {{l|en|sip}}, {{l|en|swig}}\n* {{sense|type of beverage}} {{l|en|beverage}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col4|en|title=Terms derived from ''drink'' (noun)|antidrink|cooldrink|drinkery|drinkfest|drinkie|drinkless|drinkmaking|drinkologist|drinkometer|drinksie|drinkstuff|Drinkwater|drinkwater|drinkworthy|interdrink|drinks waiter|herbal drink|roots drink\n|the {{l|en|big drink|pos=nickname for various bodies of water}}|drank|drink-driver|drink-driving|drive to drink|in the drink|straw that stirs the drink|take to drink| B-drink|be the worse for drink|black drink|call drink|can I buy you a drink|drink alert|drink hail|drink link|drink problem|drink run|drink shop|drink table|drink walking|energy drink|fizzy drink|fountain drink|gangly drink of water|have drink taken|in drink|long drink|long drink of water|meat and drink|mixed drink|pre-drink|rail drink|scrawny drink of water|skinny drink of water|junk drink|soft drink|sports drink|standard drink|strong drink|Swedish drink|tall drink of water|top-heavy with drink|well drink| drinks cabinet|drinks o'clock|drinks table|pre-drinks|the drinks are on me|cold drink money|functional drink|hold one's drink|orange drink|dew-drink|drinks trolley|red drink|predrinks|short drink|medium drink|hard drink|tall drink|table drink}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top3}}\n* {{desc|tpi|dring}}\n* {{desc|cs|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|da|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nl|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fi|drinkki|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fr|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|de|Drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|it|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|ドリンク|tr=dorinku|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pl|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|pt|drinque|drink}}\n* {{desc|sv|drink|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top-see|served beverage|beverage}}\n{{multitrans|data=\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|drank}}, {{tt|af|drankie}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|pije|f}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|суузун}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|شَرَاب|m}}, {{t|ar|مَشْرُوب|m}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|مَشْرُوب|m|tr=mašrūb}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|խմիչք}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|biuturã|f}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|bebida|f}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|içki}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|эсемлек}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|edan}}, {{tt+|eu|edari}}, {{tt+|eu|edateko}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|напо́й|m}}\n* Belizean Creole: {{tt|bzj|jrink}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|died|f}}, {{tt+|br|evaj|m}}, {{tt+|br|boeson|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|питие́|n}}, {{tt+|bg|напи́тка|f}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|ယမကာ}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|beguda|f}}, {{tt+|ca|glop|m}}\n* Cebuano: {{tt|ceb|imnunon}}\n* Chamicuro: {{tt|ccc|lajpa'sachi}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|малар}}\n* Cherokee: {{tt|chr|ᎠᏗᏔᏍᏗ}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|chakumwa}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|嘢飲}}, {{tt|yue|飲品}}, {{tt|yue|飲料|tr=jam2 liu6-2}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt+|nan-hbl|飲料|tr=ím-liāu}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|飲料}}, {{tt+|cmn|飲品}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|pití|n}}, {{tt+|cs|nápoj|m}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|drink}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|drank|m}}, {{tt+|nl|drinken|n}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|trinkaĵo}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|jook}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|juoma}}, {{tt+|fi|juotava}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|verre|m}}, {{tt+|fr|boisson|f}}\n* Friulian: {{tt|fur|bevareç}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|bebida|f}}\n* Georgian: {{tt+|ka|სასმელი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Getränk|n}}, {{q|colloquial}} {{tt+|de|Trinken|n}}, {{q|mixed drink, chiefly medical or magical}} {{tt+|de|Trank|m}}, {{tt+|de|Trunk|m}}\n* Gothic: {{tt|got|𐌳𐍂𐌰𐌲𐌺|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|ποτό|n}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{tt|grc|πόμα|n}}, {{tt|grc|ποτός|m}}\n* Haitian Creole: {{tt|ht|bwason}}\n* Hawaiian: {{tt|haw|mea inu}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|מַשְׁקֶה|m|tr=mashké}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|पेय}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|ital}}\n* Hunsrik: {{tt|hrx|Gedrenk|n}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|drykkur|m}}\n* Ido: {{tt+|io|drinkajo}}\n* Igbo: {{t|ig|ihe}} {{t|ig|ana}} {{t|ig|anu}} {{t|ig|anu}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|minum|alt=minuman}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|jooma}}\n* Ingush: {{tt|inh|малар}}\n* Irish: {{tt+|ga|deoch|f}}\n* Isoko: {{tt|iso|udi}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|bevanda|f}}, {{tt+|it|bibita|f}}, {{tt+|it|drink|m}} {{q|mainly apéritif drinks, both alcoholic and non-alcoholic, when served in bars or pubs}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|飲み物|tr=のみもの, nomimono}}, {{tt+|ja|ドリンク|tr=dorinku}}, {{tt+|ja|飲料|tr=いんりょう, inryō}}\n* Kaitag: {{t|xdq|бучча́н}}\n* Kalmyk: {{tt|xal|ундн}}\n* Kazakh: {{tt+|kk|сусын}}, {{tt+|kk|ішімдік}}\n* Khmer: {{tt+|km|ភេសជ្ជ}}, {{tt+|km|មជ្ជ}} {{qualifier|alcohol}}, {{tt+|km|ឥរា}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|음료(飮料)}}, {{tt|ko|마실 것}}, {{tt+|ko|음료수}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{tt+|ky|суусундук}}, {{tt+|ky|суусун}}, {{tt+|ky|ичкилик}}\n* Lao: {{tt+|lo|ເຄື່ອງດື່ມ}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|pōtus|m}}, {{tt|la|pōtiō|f}}, {{t|la|bibitiō|f}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|dzēriens|m}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|gėrimas|m}}, {{tt|lt|gėralas|m}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{tt|lb|Gedrénks|n}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|пијалок|m}}, {{tt|mk|пијачка|f}}\n* Malay: {{tt+|ms|minuman}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt+|ml|പാനീയം}}\n* Mongolian: {{tt+|mn|ундаа}}\n* Norman: {{tt|nrf|bouaisson|f}}\n* Ojibwe: {{tt|oj|minikwewin}}\n* Old Church Slavonic: {{tt|cu|пиво|n}}\n* Old English: {{tt|ang|drenc|m}}, {{tt|ang|wǣt|n}}\n* Oromo: {{tt|om|dhugaatii}}\n* Papiamentu: {{t|pap|bebida}}\n* Persian: {{tt+|fa|نوشابه|tr=nušâbe}}, {{tt+|fa|نوشیدنی|tr=nušidani}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{tt|pdt|Drunk|m}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|napój|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bebida|f}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|băutură|f}}\n* Romansh: {{tt|rm|bavronda|f}}, {{tt|rm|bubronda|f}}, {{tt|rm|bavranda|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|напи́ток|m}}\n* Sami:\n*: Kildin Sami: {{t|sjd|югкмушш}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|напитак|m}}, {{tt|sh|пиће|n}}, {{tt|sh|напoj|m}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|napitak|m}}, {{tt+|sh|piće|n}}, {{tt+|sh|napoj|m}}\n* Sicilian: {{tt+|scn|vìppita|f}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|nápoj|m}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|pijača|f}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{tt|dsb|piśe|n}}\n*: Upper Sorbian: {{tt|hsb|napoj|m}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|bebida|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|kinywaji}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|dryck|c}}, {{tt+|sv|dricka|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|inumin}}\n* Tajik: {{tt|tg|нӯш}}, {{tt|tg|нӯшоки}}, {{tt+|tg|машрубот}}, {{tt+|tg|нӯшоба}}\n* Tatar: {{tt+|tt|эчемлек}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|పానీయం}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|เครื่องดื่ม}}\n* Tumbuka: {{t|tum|chakumwa}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|içecek}}, {{tt+|tr|meşrubat}} {{qualifier|without alcohol}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|شربت|tr=şerbet}}, {{t|ota|شراب|tr=şarab}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|içgi}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|напі́й|m}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|مشروب|tr=mašrūb}}\n* Urhobo: {{tt|urh|udi}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|ئىچىملىك}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|ichimlik}}\n* Venetan: {{tt|vec|beùda|f}}, {{tt|vec|bevùa|f}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|ly}} {{q|glass}}, {{tt+|vi|cốc}} {{q|glass}}, {{tt+|vi|chai}} {{q|bottle or can}}\n* Volapük: {{tt|vo|dlin}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|diod|f}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|[[ohun]] [[mímu]]}}\n* ǃXóõ: {{tt|nmn|kxʻāhã}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|type of beverage}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|drank}}, {{tt|af|drankie}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|edari}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|напитка|f}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|beguda|f}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|малар}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|nápoj|m}}, {{tt+|cs|drink|m}} {{qualifier|alcohol}}, {{tt+|cs|pití|n}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|drink|c}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|drank|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|trinkaĵo}} {{qualifier|any beverage}}, {{tt|eo|drinkaĵo}} {{qualifier|alcohol}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|jook}}, {{tt+|et|drink}}\n* Ewe: {{tt|ee|nunono|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|juoma}}, {{tt+|fi|drinkki}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|boisson|f}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Getränk|n}}, {{tt+|de|Trank|m}}, {{tt+|de|Trunk|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|ποτό|n}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|ital}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|jooma}}\n* Irish: {{tt+|ga|deoch|f}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|飲料|tr=いんりょう, in'ryō}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|potio|f}}, {{tt|la|potus|m}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|dzēriens|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|пијалок|m}}, {{tt|mk|пијачка|f}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt+|ml|പാനീയം}}\n* Marathi: {{tt+|mr|पेय}}\n* Old English: {{tt|ang|drenc|m}}, {{tt|ang|wǣt|n}}\n* Persian: {{tt+|fa|نوشابه|tr=nôšâba}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{tt|pdt|Drunk|m}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|napój|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bebida|f}}, {{tt+|pt|coquetel|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|напи́ток|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|напитак|m}}, {{tt|sh|пиће|n}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|napitak|m}}, {{tt+|sh|piće|n}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|bebida|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|kinywaji}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|dryck|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|inumin}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|içecek}}, {{tt+|tr|meşrubat}} {{qualifier|without alcohol}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|شربت|tr=şerbet}}, {{t|ota|شراب|tr=şarab}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|đồ uống}}, {{tt+|vi|thức uống}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top-see|served alcoholic beverage|shot}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt|af|drankie}}, {{tt+|af|dop}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|խմիչք}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|bebida|f}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|edan}}, {{tt+|eu|edari}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|evaj|m}}, {{tt+|br|boeson|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|питие́|n}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|beguda|f}}, {{tt+|ca|glop|m}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|къаьрка}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|drink|m}}, {{tt+|cs|pití|n}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|drink}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|drank|m}}, {{tt+|nl|drinken}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|drinkaĵo}}, {{tt|eo|alkoholaĵo}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|jook}}, {{tt+|et|drink}}\n* Ewe: {{tt|ee|aha|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|juoma}}, {{tt+|fi|drinkki}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|verre|m}}\n* Georgian: {{tt+|ka|სასმელი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Getränk|n}}, {{q|specifically}} {{tt|de|[[alkoholisch|alkoholisches]] [[Getränk]]}}, {{q|chiefly ones containing liquor also}} {{tt+|de|Drink|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|ποτό|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|מַשְׁקֶה|m|tr=mashké}}, {{t+|he|מַשְׁקֶה חָרִיף|m|tr=mashké kharíf}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|ital}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|drykkur|m}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|minuman keras}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|jooma}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|bevanda|f}}, {{tt|it|[[bevanda]] [[alcolica]]}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|お酒|tr=おさけ, osake}}\n* Jeju: {{t|jje|술}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|술}}, {{tt+|ko|약주}} {{qualifier|honorific}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|potus|m}}, {{tt|la|potio|f}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|dzēriens|m}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|gėrimas|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|пијалок|m}}, {{tt|mk|пијачка|f}}\n* Mongolian: {{tt+|mn|архи}}\n* Norman: {{tt|nrf|béthe|m}}, {{tt|nrf|bouaisson|f}}, {{tt|nrf|brévage|m}}\n* Ojibwe: {{tt|oj|minikwewin}}\n* Old English: {{tt|ang|drenc|m}}, {{tt|ang|līþ|n}}\n* Persian: {{tt+|fa|مشروب|tr=mašrub}}, {{tt+|fa|باده|tr=bâda}}, {{tt|fa|درینک|tr=drink}}, {{tt|fa|نوشیدنی الکلی|tr=nôšidaniye alkoli}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|drink|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bebida|f}}, {{tt+|pt|drinque|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|băutură|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|напи́ток|m}}, {{tt+|ru|вы́пивка|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|пиће|n}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|piće|n}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|pijača|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|trago|m}}, {{tt+|es|copa|f}}, {{tt|es|alipús|m}}, {{t+|es|drink|m}} {{qualifier|Americas}}, {{t|es|drinque|m}} {{qualifier|Caribbean}}, {{t|es|plosh|m}} {{qualifier|El Salvador}}, {{t|es|tictacazo|m}} {{qualifier|El Salvador}}, {{t|es|bajapanti|m}} {{q|strong|Panama}}, {{t|es|triquis|m}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|drink|c}}, {{tt+|sv|dricka}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|inumin}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|పానీయం}}\n* Thai: {{t-needed|th}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|alkollü içecek}}, {{tt+|tr|içki}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t-check|vi|[[ly]] [[rượu]]}}{{attn|vi|was \"[[ly]] [[rượu]]\"}}, {{t-check|vi|[[cốc]] [[rượu]]}}{{attn|vi|was \"[[cốc]] rượu\" - assumed sum-of-parts; if an idiom, use <nowiki>{{t}}</nowiki> instead of <nowiki>{{t-SOP}}</nowiki>. see [[User:Kephir/gadgets/xte#Translation_fixing]]}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|ọtí}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|action of drinking}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|drink}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|пиене|n}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|мала}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|pití|n}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|tår|c}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|drinken|n}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|trinko}}\n* Estonian: {{tt|et|joomine}}, {{tt|et|jooming}}\n* Ewe: {{tt|ee|nunono|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|kulaus}}, {{tt+|fi|siemaus}}, {{tt+|fi|hörppy}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|boire}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|bebida|f}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|სმა}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Trinken|n}}, {{tt+|de|Trinkerei|f}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|πόση|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{tt|grc|πόσις|f}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|שתייה|alt=שְׁתִיָּה|tr=shtiyá|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|ivás}}\n* Irish: {{tt+|ga|deoch|f}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|bevuta|f}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|飲用|tr=いんよう, in'yō}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|potio|f}}, {{tt|la|potus|m}}, {{tt|la|bibitiō|f}} {{q|Medieval}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|malks|m}}, {{tt|lv|dzeršana|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|gėrimas|f}}, {{tt+|lt|išgėrimas|m}}\n* Marathi: {{t-check|mr|पिणे}}, {{t+check|mr|पान}}, {{t-check|mr|[[पिण्याची]] [[क्रिया]]}}{{attn|mr|was \"पिण्याची क्रिया\" - not sure how it is supposed to be linked}}\n* Neapolitan: {{tt|nap|véppata}}\n* Old English: {{tt|ang|drync|m}}\n* Persian: {{tt+|fa|نوشیدن|tr=nôšidan}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|picie|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bebida|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|питьё|n}}\n* Sami:\n*: Kildin Sami: {{t|sjd|югкмушш}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|požirek|m}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|beber|m}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|nywa|alt=kunywa}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|drickande|n}}, {{tt+|sv|klunk|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|pag-inom}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|içmek}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|uống}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|alcoholic beverages in general}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|drank}}, {{tt+|af|dop}}\n* Arabic:\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{tt|ary|شراب|tr=šrāb}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|alkohol}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|алкохолни напитки|p}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|къаьрка}}, {{tt|ce|алкоголин малар}}, {{tt|ce|спирт}}, {{tt|ce|корта бахош долу малар}}, {{tt|ce|алкоголь}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|alkohol}}, {{tt|da|spiritus}}\n* Ewe: {{tt|ee|aha|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|alkoholijuoma}}\n* Georgian: {{t-needed|ka}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Drink|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|ποτό|n}}, {{tt+|el|οινοπνευματώδη|n-p}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|מַשְׁקָאוֹת חָרִיפִים|m-p|tr=mashka'ót kharifím}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|szeszes ital}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|酒|tr=さけ, sake}}, {{tt+|ja|お酒|tr=おさけ, osake}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|potus|m}}, {{tt|la|potio|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|пијалок|m}}, {{tt|mk|пијачка|f}}\n* Marathi: {{tt|mr|अपेयपेय}}, {{tt|mr|दारू}}, {{tt|mr|मदिरा}}\n* Persian: {{tt+|fa|می|tr=may}}, {{tt+|fa|مشروب|tr=mašrôb}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|trunki|p}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bebida|f}}, {{tt+|pt|álcool|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|вы́пивка|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|пиће|n}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|piće|n}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|alipús|m}}, {{t|es|chínguere|m}} {{qualifier|Mexico}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|dricka}}, {{tt+|sv|sprit}}, {{tt+|sv|alkohol}}\n* Thai: {{t-needed|th}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|rượu}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|\"the drink\"- colloquially, any body of water}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|potus|m}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|dricka|n}}, {{tt+|sv|spad|n}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Breton: {{t+check|br|died|f}}, {{t+check|br|evaj|m}}\n* German:\n*: Old High German: {{t-check|goh|trunch}}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{t-check|gug|jey'urã}}\n* Interlingua: {{t-check|ia|bibita}}, {{t-check|ia|biberage}}\n* Low German: {{t+check|nds|drinken|n}}\n* Old English: {{t-check|ang|drync}}\n* Old Norse: {{t-check|non|drykkr|m}}\n* Thai: {{t+check|th|เหล้า|tr=lao}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{cln|en|strong verbs|irregular verbs}}\n{{C|en|Food and drink|Liquids|Units of measure}}\n{{cln|en|autohyponyms}}<!-- drink any liquid vs. drink alcohol -->\n\n==Afrikaans==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|af|nl|drinken}}, from {{inh|af|dum|drinken}}, from {{inh|af|odt|drinkan}}, from {{inh|af|gem-pro|*drinkaną}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|af|LL-Q14196 (afr)-Iwan.Aucamp-drink.wav}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{af-verb}}\n\n# to [[#English|drink]]\n\n==Czech==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|cs|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\n{{bor+|cs|en|drink}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{cs-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cs-noun|m-in}}\n\n# {{l|en|drink}} {{gloss|a (mixed) alcoholic beverage}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{cs-ndecl|m}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:cs:PSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:SSJC}}\n\n{{C|cs|Alcoholic beverages}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|da|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\nFrom {{bor|da|en|drink}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|en|s}}\n\n# {{l|en|drink}}; a (mixed) alcoholic beverage\n\n====Inflection====\n{{da-noun-infl|en|drinks|drinksene|||drinks'}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|da|sjus|g=c}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:DDO}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/drɪŋk/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-drink.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|drink}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|ɪŋk|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|nl|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|en|drink}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|m|-s|-}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|Belgium}} a social event were [[beverage]]s are served, with or without snacks, e.g. as a celebration\n# {{lb|nl|Netherlands}} a [[beverage]], a {{l|en|drink}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|nl|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|nl|drinken||bare-verb}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\n{{bor+|fr|en|drink}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|dring_k}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lyokoï-drink.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# a [[reception]] or [[after-party|afterparty]] where alcohol is served\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|it|:ubor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\n{{ubor|it|en|drink}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|^ì<r:DiPI>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m|#,drinks<l:dated>}}\n\n# {{l|en|drink}} {{gloss|served beverage and mixed beverage}}\n#: {{syn|it|bevanda}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|it\n|year=1970\n|tlr=Mercedes Giardini\n|title=Il padrino\n|original={{w|The Godfather (novel)|The Godfather}}\n|by=w:Mario Puzo\n|publisher=dall'Oglio editore\n|location=Milan\n|chapter=Ⅻ\n|page=160\n|text=«Non sono in forma con la voce», rispose. «E con tutta sincerità, sono stufo di sentirmi cantare». Sorseggiarono i '''drinks'''.\n|t=\"My voice is not doing well\", he replied. \"And, in all honesty, I'm tired of hearing myself singing\". They sipped their '''drinks'''.\n}}\n#* {{quote-av\n|it\n|title=La grande bellezza\n|role=Jep Gambardella\n|actor=Toni Servillo\n|writer=w:Paolo Sorrentino\n|year=2013\n|time=01:39:42\n|passage=Io berrò molti '''drink''', ma non così tanti da diventare molesto.\n|t=I'll drink many '''drinks''', but not so many to become annoying.}}\n\n===References===\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:it:Trec}}\n\n==Low German==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|nds|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|nds|drinken||1|s}}\n\n==North Frisian==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|frr|drank||Föhr-Amrum}}\n* {{alt|frr|drinke||Halligen}}\n* {{alt|frr|drainke||Mooring}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|frr|ofs|drinka}}, from {{inh|frr|gmw-pro|*drinkan}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|frr|[d̥rɪŋk]|a=Sylt}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|frr|verb|present}}\n\n# {{lb|frr|Sylt|Heligolandic}} to {{l|en|drink}}\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{frr-Sylt-conj-table|inf_2=drinken|ppp=drunken|pres_2=drinkst|pres_3=drinkt|past_1=droonk|past_2=droonkst}}\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:}}\n[[File:Margarita.jpg|thumb|drink]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|pl|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>|text=+|tree=1}} {{dbt|pl|dręk|trunek}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=Pl-drink.ogg}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-anml}}\n\n# [[cocktail]], {{l|en|drink}} {{gl|served alcoholic beverage}}\n#* {{quote-song|pl|year=2011|artist=Poparzeni Kawą Trzy|title=Kawałek do tańca|passage=Jeszcze trochę do północy<br/>'''drink''' jak zagubiony pocisk<br/>strzelił mocno mi do głowy<br/>coraz trudniej się wysłowić.|t=There's still some time before midnight<br/>The '''drink''', like a lost bullet,<br/>shot me right in the head<br/>it's getting harder and harder to speak.}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-decl-noun-m-anml}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pl|title=verbs|drinkować<g:impf>}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:WSJP}}\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n\n{{C|pl|Cocktails}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|pt|en|drink}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|drinque}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|m|#s}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|pt|drinque}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n[[File:Dry Martini-2.jpg|thumb|250px|en drink ({{l|sv|cocktail}})]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|sv|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\nFrom {{bor|sv|en|drink}}. {{doublet|sv|dryck}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sv|/drɪŋk/}}\n* {{audio|sv|Sv-en drink.ogg|a=Gotland}}\n* {{rhymes|sv|ɪŋk|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# a {{l|en|drink}} ((mixed) alcoholic beverage)\n#: {{ux|sv|ta en '''drink'''|enjoy a '''drink'''}}\n#* {{quote-song|sv|year=2021|author=w:Hooja|title=Banan, Melon, Kiwi & Citron|text=Banan, melon, kiwi och citron / De häller det i '''drinken''' och säger \"den är god\"|t=Banana, melon, kiwi and lemon / They pour it in '''the drink''' and tell you \"it's good\"}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n''Drink'' in the more general sense of ''beverage'' is {{m|sv|dryck}}.\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-infl-noun-c-ar}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|sv\n|drinkare\n|drinkblandare\n|drinklista\n|drinkpinne\n|drinktilltugg\n|fördrink\n|kaffedrink\n|mjölkdrink\n|paraplydrink\n|proteindrink\n|softdrink\n|stilldrink\n|välkomstdrink\n}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|sv|dryck}}\n* {{l|sv|grogg}}\n* {{l|sv|sup}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saob}}\n\n{{C|sv|Alcoholic beverages}}\n\n==West Frisian==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|fy|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|fy|drinke||1|s|pres}}\n# {{inflection of|fy|drinke||imp}}\n\n==Yola==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|yol|:inh|enm:drinken}}\nFrom {{inh|yol|enm|drinken}}, from {{inh|yol|ang|drincan}}, from {{inh|yol|gmw-pro|*drinkan}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|yol|/drɪŋk/}}\n* {{IPA|yol|[ˈd̪rɪnkən]<ref:{{R:Muirithe 1990|page=150}}>}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|yol|verb}}\n\n# to {{l|en|drink}}\n#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=THE WEDDEEN O BALLYMORE|number=4|page=96<ref>{{R:Poole 1867|page=96}}</ref>|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage='''Drink''' a heall to a breede. \"Shud with, a voorneen.\"|translation='''Drink''' a health to the bride, \"Here's to you, my dear.\"}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|yol|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|drink}}\n#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=VERSES IN ANSWER TO THE WEDDEEN O BALLYMORE|page=98|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage=Tibbès an crockès wee '''drink''' war ee-felt.|translation=[Tubs and crocks were filled with '''drink'''.]}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>"}}